sentences: Axel Carl William Grandjean (9 March 1847 - 11 February 1932) was a Danish composer and conductor.
He was one of the first students at the Royal Danish Academy of Music with dignified teachers such  as Niels Gade, Johann Peter Emilius Hartmann, August Winding and Johann Christian Gebauer.
That same year he took on a study trip to Germany and Paris.
After his return he worked as a music teacher and now as a conductor.
In 1899-1918 he was at the Danish Royal Theater.
He also composed many songs and piano arrangements, including a 3 volume work of a variety of songs from the 19th century Vaudeville.
